报告显示草根音乐场馆面临“灾难”：“大公司和场馆现在必须为此负责” https://www.nme.com/news/music/report-shows-disaster-faceing-grassroots-music-venues-the-big-companies-and-arenas-are-now-going-to-have-to-对此 3576307 的回答？utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=报告显示面临灾难的草根音乐场馆大公司和竞技场现在将不得不-对此的回答Andrew TrendellWed, 24 Jan 2024 15:14:57 +0000 Music NewsNews https://www.nme.com/?p=3576307 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/novelist_brudenell_venues_report_2000.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="利兹布鲁德内尔社交俱乐部的小说家（摄影：Visionhaus/Getty Images）" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/novelist_brudenell_venues_report_2000.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/novelist_brudenell_venues_report_2000-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/novelist_brudenell_venues_report_2000-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/novelist_brudenell_venues_report_2000-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/novelist_brudenell_venues_report_2000-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/novelist_brudenell_venues_report_2000-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>音乐场馆信托基金的报告显示了失去的和面临的风险，他们警告说：“我们正在失去下一代英国人才，因为我们懒得去纠正。”</p><p>这篇<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/report-shows-disaster-facing-grassroots-music-venues-the-big-companies-and-arenas-are-now-going-to-have-to-answer-for-this-3576307">帖子展示了草根音乐场所面临的“灾难”：“大公司和场馆现在将不得不为此负责”，</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/novelist_brudenell_venues_report_2000.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="利兹布鲁德内尔社交俱乐部的小说家（摄影：Visionhaus/Getty Images）" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/novelist_brudenell_venues_report_2000.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/novelist_brudenell_venues_report_2000-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/novelist_brudenell_venues_report_2000-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/novelist_brudenell_venues_report_2000-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/novelist_brudenell_venues_report_2000-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/novelist_brudenell_venues_report_2000-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>一份新发布的报告显示了 2023 年英国草根音乐场馆遭受的“灾难”，要求对更大的场馆征收门票税和更广泛的行业进行投资的呼声越来越高。</p><ul><li> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/2023-was-worst-year-for-venue-closures-while-no-one-in-music-industry-seems-to-care-say-mvt-3562266"><strong>阅读更多：</strong> MVT 表示，2023 年是“场馆关闭最糟糕的一年”，而“音乐行业似乎没有人关心”</a></li></ul><p>去年，音乐场馆信托基金<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-venue-trust-annual-report-government-action-arena-investment-frank-turner-talent-pipeline-3389434">在议会大厦提交了第一份年度报告，警告英国的草根演出空间正在“走向悬崖”，</a>除非政府采取紧急行动和新的大型场馆的投资。在发出严厉警告称<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/uk-to-lose-10-per-cent-of-grassroots-venues-in-2023-as-calls-grow-for-rest-of-industry-to-invest-3499727">英国将在 2023 年失去 10% 的草根音乐场馆后，</a> MVT 和该行业的其他人士在年底时<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/2023-was-worst-year-for-venue-closures-while-no-one-in-music-industry-seems-to-care-say-mvt-3562266">告诉<em>NME</em> 2023 年是“场馆关闭最糟糕的一年</a>”，而“没有人”音乐界似乎很关心”。</p><p>现在，MVT 分享了<a href="https://www.musicvenuetrust.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/MVT_2023-Annual-Report_Digital.pdf?fbclid=IwAR2rm8d7s65E4d0ZHqNgvAnFIuVAA_CttOf5yqRKFR9onVTJPNkkwoKI4vk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">2023 年该行业状况的完整报告</a>。据报道，在“最具挑战性的一年”的主要调查结果中，去年有 125 个英国场馆放弃了现场音乐表演，其中超过一半已经完全关闭， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/legendary-music-venue-moles-in-bath-closes-after-45-years-today-is-a-very-sad-day-3553756">其中包括传奇的巴斯 Moles 场馆</a>。据报道，一些更紧迫的制约因素包括能源价格飙升、房东提高地税金额、供应成本、营业费率、许可问题、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/manchester-night-day-cardiff-fuel-post-lockdown-noise-complaints-venues-3103934">噪音投诉</a>以及<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-venue-trust-thank-help-gigs-return-2021-2842425">COVID-19 的持续冲击波</a>。</p><p>总体而言，场馆租金上涨了37.5%，而平均运营利润率仅为0.5%。</p><p> <em>NME</em>昨晚（1 月 24 日星期三）参加了在威斯敏斯特举行的发布会，现场描绘了英国场景的鲜明形象——尽管观众显然对现场音乐有着巨大的渴望。 </p><blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/p/C2eb1B6tPYY/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:658px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);"><div style="padding:16px;"><div style="background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 50%; flex-grow: 0; height: 40px; margin-right: 14px; width: 40px;"></div><div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; flex-grow: 1; justify-content: center;"><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px; width: 100px;"></div><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; width: 60px;"></div></div></div><div style="padding: 19% 0;"></div><div style="display:block; height:50px; margin:0 auto 12px; width:50px;"><svg width="50px" height="50px" viewBox="0 0 60 60" version="1.1" xmlns="https://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="https://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><g stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><g transform="translate(-511.000000, -20.000000)" fill="#000000"><g><path d="M556.869,30.41 C554.814,30.41 553.148,32.076 553.148,34.131 C553.148,36.186 554.814,37.852 556.869,37.852 C558.924,37.852 560.59,36.186 560.59,34.131 C560.59,32.076 558.924,30.41 556.869,30.41 M541,60.657 C535.114,60.657 530.342,55.887 530.342,50 C530.342,44.114 535.114,39.342 541,39.342 C546.887,39.342